Class IntegerStringnum

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blockwithme.util.proto.stringnum.Stringnum

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<String>, Collection<String>, List<String>, Set<String>

    public class IntegerStringnum
extends Stringnum
    IntegerStringnum is a Stringnum that only accepts integers > 0, in the natural order. Note that if onNewString() fails, the object will be inconsistent and cannot be safely used anymore. TODO Test
